column5: With all the great Steelhead reports lately, I wanted to share a few pictures of the ones I've been lucky enough to land over the last couple of weeks. The past week has been tough with the lack of rain, but I found switching up baits, even changing between different cures of Salmon roe, helped to trigger some much anticipated hits.   A colourful fall Buck.   Here's another angle.    Yet another male. Been catching a lot of them lately.    This was one of my larger catches.    This one put up a great fight. He went for the sticks, but my leader held.
That last one is a brute!
Nice Dude!! Maaaaan.... with all this work around the house, and seeing all these STEELHEAD reports, I'm DYING to get out there!!  Keep bringing in the reports!
Beautiful fish Andrew...Nicely done  Thought you would've been out today with the other guys...Ran into them today...F1 is done for the season
i'll trade you reels!!   yeah, why didn't you come out today?? we hammered them with cheese colour singles today
beautiful fish that last one. cheers broseph.

Thanks Bill! Pictures don't even do that one justice, but I still got a long way to go before I start dropping the beauties you do.   Don't remind me F1 is over, it's the longest off-season for any sport. I guess I'll just have to go fishing in the meantime  Let's get out there soon.  Singles eh? I'll try that next time out!
Great pics! Awesome fish!  Thanks for sharing  p.-
Great job Jet Nice steel!!! Leechman
